==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Espial
<hw>Es*pi"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. & Norm. F.
<ets>espiaille</ets>. See <er>Espy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of espying; notice; discovery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Screened from <qex>espial</qex> by the jutting cape.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who espies; a spy; a scout.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Their <xex>espials</xex> . . . brought
word.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Espier</ent>⟦br⟧
